transcript.text: Hello everyone, welcome to this tutorial on how to set up the Hire a designer option in on Print shop.
Before moving ahead, we must first understand why this option is needed.

There might be instances where the customer of your store may demand a designer when they don't want any of the templates you have provided for the customization, or in some cases they want to create a custom design for the product.
In such cases, this option becomes significant.
So let's enable this option.
Then set up additional options and finally add the pricing.
Here we will enable the higher Designer option for the flyer product.
For this, navigate to the product section, locate the flyer product, click on the Action drop down menu and select the Edit option.
On the Edit screen, you will find the higher Designer check box under the Configuration section.
Just check this box to enable and display this action button on the front door.
On the front door, when the customer browses the flyer product on the product detail page, they can find the Lettuce Design for you option here.
By default, option No will be selected.
Once the customer selects yes, the pricing will be updated.
Now let's see how you can set up the cost for this option.
To define the cost, navigate to the Settings tab and then click on the Pricing tab.
Here you can enter the cost for this option.
Let's enter $50.00 for now.
Please note that you need to define the higher designer cost for different products individually, so now you know where the cost comes from.
As soon as the customers choose to hire a designer for their product design needs, the Action button will appear below the price calculator.
Clicking on this option will take the customer to the Product Additional Info page where they can only find the option with Yes selected.
To get more information from the customers, we need to have a few additional options.
To create additional options, let's go back to the Admin panel and move to the Options tab.
We are creating three additional options for now, Company Name, Upload File, and Additional Information.
Click on the Add button, enter the title as Company Name.
Select the Type as text box and enable the Higher Designer setting to allow this additional option to display on the front store.
When the customer opts for the designer, save the details.
Similarly, to allow the customer to upload their logo or images, create an option by entering a title and selecting Upload File as type and enabling the higher designer setting.
Save the details and then create the third option on the front door.
You can now see the three additional options.
The customer can provide the required details and then place the order.
After placing the order, the customer can review the order product details along with the higher designer cost.
That's it.
This way, you can set the higher designer options for any of your products.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
